{"title_page": "Faith Torrez", "text_new": "{{short description|American artistic gymnast}}\n{{Infobox gymnast\n| name            = Faith Torrez\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| fullname        = \n| altname         = \n| nickname        = \n| country         = {{flag|United States}}\n| regionsrepresented = \n| formercountry   = \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|2003|12|09}}\n| birth_place     = [[Libertyville, Illinois]], U.S.\n| hometown        = \n| residence       = \n| training        = \n| height          = <!-- \"X cm\", \"X m\"  or \"X ft Y in\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| weight          = <!-- \"X kg\", \"X lb\" or \"X st Y lb\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| discipline      = WAG\n| level           = Senior International Elite\n| natlteam        = 2020\u2013Present ([[United States women's national gymnastics team|US]])\n| club            = Legacy Elite Gymnastics LLC\n| gym             = \n| collegeteam     = [[Oklahoma Sooners women's gymnastics|Oklahoma Sooners]]\n| headcoach       = Jiani Wu\n| assistcoach     = Yuejiu Li, Anna Li\n| formercoach     = \n| choreographer   = \n| music           = \n| eponymousskills = \n| retired         = \n| worldranking    = \n| show-medals     = yes\n| medaltemplates  =\n{{MedalCountry | the {{USA}} }}\n}}\n\n'''Faith Torrez''' (born December 9 2003) is an American [[Artistic gymnastics|artistic gymnast]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/pages/athletes/athleteListDetail.html?id=391458|title=USA Gymnastics {{!}} Faith Torrez|website=usagym.org|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> She became a member of the [[United States women's national gymnastics team|United States national team]] in 2020<ref name=\":2\" /> and made her international debut at 2020 Gymnix International, winning two golds and a bronze.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Junior ===\nTorrez began gymnastics in 2008.<ref name=\":0\" /> As a junior, she competed at the Women's Junior Olympic National Championships in 2016, 2017 and 2018. She won gold on floor exercise in 2017. In 2018, she won all-around and balance beam gold, as well as floor exercise silver.<ref name=\":0\" /> In 2018, she competed at the [[Nastia Liukin Cup]] for the first time and won all-around bronze.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/pages/post.html?PostID=21413|title=Bryant, Vetter win 2018 Nastia Liukin Cup|website=USA Gymnastics|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> She was the top scorer on floor with 9.600; her highest score of the competition was a 9.675 on vault.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n=== Senior ===\n\n==== 2019 ====\nTorrez became a senior in 2019. She competed at the Nastia Liukin Cup in March, finishing seventh all-around.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/PDFs/Results/2019/w_19nlc_sr.pdf|title=2019 Nastia Liukin Cup Meet Results - Seniors|last=USA Gymnastics|first=|date=1 March 2019|website=usagym.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> At the American Classic in June, Torrez won all-around gold, finishing first on vault, second on uneven bars and floor exercise, and third on balance beam.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/pages/post.html?PostID=24026|title=Torrez, Alipio win all-around titles at 2019 American Classic|website=USA Gymnastics|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> In July at the GK US Classic, she finished sixth on balance beam and eighth all-around.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/PDFs/Results/2019/w_19classic_sr.pdf|title=2019 GK US Classic Meet Results|last=USA Gymnastics|first=|date=20 July 2019|website=usagym.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> At the [[2019 U.S. National Gymnastics Championships|US Gymnastics Championships]] in August, Torrez finished 14th all-around.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/PDFs/Results/2019/w_19champs_sraa.pdf|title=2019 US Championships - Women Day 2 Meet Results - Multi|last=USA Gymnastics|first=|date=11 August 2019|website=usagym.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\n==== 2020 ====\nTorrez was added to the senior national team on March 3 2020.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/pages/women/history/past_nat_teams_sr.html|title=USA Gymnastics {{!}} Women's Past Senior National Teams|website=usagym.org|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> She made her international debut on March 6-8 at Gymnix International. With teammates [[Lilly Lippeatt]], [[MyKayla Skinner]] and [[Emily Lee]], she won team gold. Individually, she captured balance beam gold with a score of 13.966 and uneven bars bronze with a score of 12.966.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/pages/post.html?PostID=25320|title=USA wins senior and junior team titles, 10 individual titles at 2020 Gymnix International|website=USA Gymnastics|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Torrez, Faith}}\n[[Category:2003 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American female artistic gymnasts]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American artistic gymnast}}\n{{Infobox gymnast\n| name            = Faith Torrez\n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| fullname        = \n| altname         = \n| nickname        = \n| country         = {{flag|United States}}\n| regionsrepresented = \n| formercountry   = \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|2003|12|09}}\n| birth_place     = [[Libertyville, Illinois]], U.S.\n| hometown        = \n| residence       = \n| training        = \n| height          = <!-- \"X cm\", \"X m\"  or \"X ft Y in\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| weight          = <!-- \"X kg\", \"X lb\" or \"X st Y lb\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| discipline      = WAG\n| level           = Senior International Elite\n| natlteam        = 2019\u2013Present ([[United States women's national gymnastics team|US]])\n| club            = Legacy Elite Gymnastics LLC\n| gym             = \n| collegeteam     = [[Oklahoma Sooners women's gymnastics|Oklahoma Sooners]]\n| headcoach       = Jiani Wu\n| assistcoach     = Yuejiu Li, Anna Li\n| formercoach     = \n| choreographer   = \n| music           = \n| eponymousskills = \n| retired         = \n| worldranking    = \n| show-medals     = yes\n| medaltemplates  =\n{{MedalCountry | the {{USA}} }}\n}}\n\n'''Faith Torrez''' (born December 9 2003) is an American [[Artistic gymnastics|artistic gymnast]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/pages/athletes/athleteListDetail.html?id=391458|title=USA Gymnastics {{!}} Faith Torrez|website=usagym.org|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> She became a member of the [[United States women's national gymnastics team|United States national team]] in 2019 and made her international debut at 2020 Gymnix International, winning two golds and a bronze.\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Junior ===\nTorrez began gymnastics in 2008.<ref name=\":0\" /> As a junior, she competed at the Women's Junior Olympic National Championships in 2016, 2017 and 2018. She won gold on floor exercise in 2017. In 2018, she won all-around and balance beam gold, as well as floor exercise silver.<ref name=\":0\" /> In 2018, she competed at the Nastia Liukin Cup for the first time and won all-around bronze.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/pages/post.html?PostID=21413|title=Bryant, Vetter win 2018 Nastia Liukin Cup|website=USA Gymnastics|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> She was the top scorer on floor with 9.600; her highest score of the competition was a 9.675 on vault.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n=== Senior ===\n\n==== 2019 ====\nTorrez became a senior in 2019. She competed at the Nastia Liukin Cup in March, finishing seventh all-around.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/PDFs/Results/2019/w_19nlc_sr.pdf|title=2019 Nastia Liukin Cup Meet Results - Seniors|last=USA Gymnastics|first=|date=1 March 2019|website=usagym.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> At the American Classic in June, Torrez won all-around gold, finishing first on vault, second on uneven bars and floor exercise, and third on balance beam.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/pages/post.html?PostID=24026|title=Torrez, Alipio win all-around titles at 2019 American Classic|website=USA Gymnastics|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> In July at the GK US Classic, she finished sixth on balance beam and eighth all-around.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/PDFs/Results/2019/w_19classic_sr.pdf|title=2019 GK US Classic Meet Results|last=USA Gymnastics|first=|date=20 July 2019|website=usagym.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> At the US Gymnastics Championships in August, Torrez finished 14th all-around.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/PDFs/Results/2019/w_19champs_sraa.pdf|title=2019 US Championships - Women Day 2 Meet Results - Multi|last=USA Gymnastics|first=|date=11 August 2019|website=usagym.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\n==== 2020 ====\nTorrez was added to the senior national team on March 3 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/pages/women/history/past_nat_teams_sr.html|title=USA Gymnastics {{!}} Women's Past Senior National Teams|website=usagym.org|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> She made her international debut on March 6-8 at Gymnix International. With teammates [[Lilly Lippeatt]], [[MyKayla Skinner]] and [[Emily Lee]], she won team gold. Individually, she captured balance beam gold with a score of 13.966 and uneven bars bronze with a score of 12.966.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usagym.org/pages/post.html?PostID=25320|title=USA wins senior and junior team titles, 10 individual titles at 2020 Gymnix International|website=USA Gymnastics|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n\