e majority]]: 29<br/>[[Two-thirds majority]]: 37\n| structure1     = JohorDUN.svg\n| structure1_res = 250px\n| political_groups1 = ({{as of|2020|02|27}})<br/>\n'''[[State governments of Malaysia|Government]] (29):'''<br/>\n{{colorbox|{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}}} [[Perikatan Nasional]] (29)\n*{{Color box|{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}}} [[Barisan Nasional]] (16)<br/> \n**{{Color box|{{United Malays National Organisation/meta/color}}}} [[United Malay National Organisation|UMNO]] (14)\n**{{Color box|{{Malaysian Indian Congress/meta/color}}}} [[Malaysian Indian Congress|MIC]] (2)\n*{{Color box|{{Malaysian United Indigenous Party/meta/shading}}}} [[Malaysian United Indigenous Party|BERSATU]] (11)<br/>\n*{{Color box|{{Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party/meta/color}}}} [[Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]] (1)<br/>\n*{{Color box|{{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}}} [[Independent (politician)|Independent]] (1)\n\n'''[[Opposition (Malaysia)|Opposition]] (27):'''<br/>\n{{Color box|{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}}} [[Pakatan Harapan]] (27)<br/>\n*{{Color box|{{Democratic Action Party/meta/color}}}} [[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|DAP]] (14)\n*{{Color box|{{National Trust Party (Malaysia)/meta/color}}}} [[National Trust Party (Malaysia)|AMANAH]] (9)\n*{{Color box|{{People's Justice Party (Malaysia)/meta/color}}}} [[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|PKR]] (4)\n\n| committees1    = {{Collapsible list |title = 4 |Public Accounts Committee|Rules of Proceedings Committee|Right and Privileges Committee|Committee of Selection}}\n| voting_system1 = [[Plurality voting system|Plurality]]: [[First-past-the-post voting|First-past-the-post]] (56 single-member constituencies)\n| last_election1 = [[Johor state election, 2018|9 May 2018]]\n| next_election1 = [[Next Johor state election|28 August 2023 or earlier]]\n| meeting_place = [[Sultan Ismail Building]], [[Kota Iskandar, Johor|Kota Iskandar]], [[Iskandar Puteri]], [[Johor]]\n| meeting_place2 = [[Sultan Ibrahim Building]], [[Johor Bahru]], [[Johor]]\n| website       = {{URL|http://www.johor.gov.my/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Johor State Legislative Assembly''' ({{lang-ms|Dewan Undangan Negeri Johor}}) is the [[unicameral]] [[Dewan Undangan Negeri|legislature]] of the [[Malaysia]]n [[States of Malaysia|state]] of [[Johor]]. It is composed of 56 members who are elected from [[single-member constituencies]] throughout the state. [[Elections in Malaysia|Elections]] are held no more than five years apart, along with elections to the [[Dewan Rakyat|federal parliament]] and other state assemblies (except [[Sarawak]]).\n\nThe State Assembly convenes at [[Sultan Ismail Building]] in [[Kota Iskandar, Johor|Kota Iskandar]], [[Iskandar Puteri]].\n\n==Current composition==\n{{for|a complete list of members|Malaysian State Assembly Representatives (2018-)#Johor}}\n{| style=\"width:40em;\"\n|-  style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"color:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}};\" |'''PN'''\n| style=\"color:{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}};\" colspan=3|'''PH'''\n|-  style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}; color:white;width:50.00%;\" |'''29'''\n|  style=\"background:{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}; color:white;width:50.00%;\" colspan=3|'''27'''\n|-\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| style=\"background:{{United Malays National Organisation/meta/color}}; color:white;width:25%;\"|'''14'''\n| style=\"background:{{Malaysian United Indigenous Party/meta/shading}}; color:white;width:19.64%;\"|'''11'''\n| style=\"background:{{Malaysian Indian Congress/meta/color}}; color:white;width:3.57%;\"|'''2'''\n|'''1'''\n| style=\"background:{{Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party/meta/color}}; color:white;width:1.79%;\"|'''1'''\n| style=\"background:{{Democratic Action Party/meta/color}}; color:white;width:25%;\"|'''14'''\n| style=\"background:{{National Trust Party (Malaysia)/meta/color}}; color:white;width:16.07%;\"|'''9'''\n| style=\"background:{{People's Justice Party (Malaysia)/meta/col