Rules of Proceedings Committee|Right and Privileges Committee|Committee of Selection}}\n| voting_system1 = [[Plurality voting system|Plurality]]: [[First-past-the-post voting|First-past-the-post]] (56 single-member constituencies)\n| last_election1 = [[Johor state election, 2018|9 May 2018]]\n| next_election1 = [[Next Johor state election|28 August 2023 or earlier]]\n| meeting_place = [[Sultan Ismail Building]], [[Kota Iskandar, Johor|Kota Iskandar]], [[Iskandar Puteri]], [[Johor]]\n| meeting_place2 = [[Sultan Ibrahim Building]], [[Johor Bahru]], [[Johor]]\n| website       = {{URL|http://www.johor.gov.my/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Johor State Legislative Assembly''' ({{lang-ms|Dewan Undangan Negeri Johor}}) is the [[unicameral]] [[Dewan Undangan Negeri|legislature]] of the [[Malaysia]]n [[States of Malaysia|state]] of [[Johor]]. It is composed of 56 members who are elected from [[single-member constituencies]] throughout the state. [[Elections in Malaysia|Elections]] are held no more than five years apart, along with elections to the [[Dewan Rakyat|federal parliament]] and other state assemblies (except [[Sarawak]]).\n\nThe State Assembly convenes at [[Sultan Ismail Building]] in [[Kota Iskandar, Johor|Kota Iskandar]], [[Iskandar Puteri]].\n\n==Current composition==\n{{for|a complete list of members|Malaysian State Assembly Representatives (2018-)#Johor}}\n{| style=\"width:40em;\"\n|-  style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"color:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}};\" |''PN'''\n| style=\"color:{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}};\" colspan=3|'''PH'''\n|-  style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"background:{{Barisan Nasional/meta/color}}; color:white;width:50.00%;\" |'''29'''\n|  style=\"background:{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}; color:white;width:50.00%;\" colspan=3|'''27'''\n|-\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| style=\"background:{{United Malays National Organisation/meta/color}}; color:white;width:25%;\"|'''14'''\n| style=\"background:{{Malaysian Unite