|| bgcolor={{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}| {{Font color|white|N51 Bukit Batu|link=Bukit Batu (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N41 Puteri Wangsa|link=Puteri Wangsa (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N28 Mengkibol|link=Mengkibol (state constituency)}} || || || \n|-\n| || || || Vacant || bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\"| {{Font color|white|N38 Penawar|link=Penawar (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N18 Sri Medan|link=Sri Medan (state constituency)}}|| || || || || bgcolor={{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}| {{Font color|white|N42 Johor Jaya|link=Johor Jaya (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N48 Skudai|link=Skudai (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N29 Mahkota|link=Mahkota (state constituency)}} || || || \n|-\n| || || || Vacant || bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\"| {{Font color|white|N1 Buloh Kasap|link=Buloh Kasap (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N31 Kahang|link=Kahang (state constituency)}}|| || || || || bgcolor={{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}| {{Font color|white|N49 Kota Iskandar (Opposition Leader)|link=Kota Iskandar (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N13 Simpang Jeram|link=Simpang Jeram (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Independent/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|black|N3 Pemanis|link=Pemanis (state constituency)}} || || || \n|-\n| || || || Vacant || bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\"| {{Font color|white|N56 Kukup|link=Kukup (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N20 Semarang|link=Semarang (state constituency)}}|| || || || || bgcolor={{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}| {{Font color|white|N21 Parit Yaani|link=Parit Yaani (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N47 Kempas|link=Kempas (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N4 Kemelah|link=Kemelah (state constituency)}} || || || \n|-\n| || || || Vacant || bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\"| {{Font color|white|N33 Tenggaroh|link=Tenggaroh (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N53 Benut (Menteri Besar)|link=Benut (state constituency)}}|| || || || || bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\"| {{Font color|white|''N7 Bukit Kepong''|link=Bukit Kepong (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N9 Gambir|link=Gambir (state constituency)}}|| bgcolor=\"{{Perikatan Nasional/meta/color}}\" |{{Font color|white|N44 Larkin|link=Larkin (state constituency)}} || || || \n|-\n| || || || || || || || || colspan=2 | Secretary || || || || || || || || \n|-\n| || || || colspan=3| Sergeant-at-Arm || || || colspan=2 bgcolor={{Pakatan Harapan/meta/color}}| {{color|white|Speaker}} || || || State Secretary || State Legal Advisor || State Financial Officer || || || \n|-\n| || || || || || || || || colspan=2 | Sultan || || || || || || || || \n|}\n</div>\n\n==Role==\nThe Johor State Legislative Assembly's main function is to enact laws that apply in the state. It is also the forum for members to voice their opinions on the state government's policies and implementation of those policies. Under the Privileges, Immunities and Powers Ordinance 1963, assemblymen are given the right to freely discuss current issues such as public complaints. On financial matters, the Assembly approves [[Appropriation bill|supply]] to the government and ensures that the funds are spent as approved and in the tax-payers' interest.\n\nThe [[Johor State Executive Council|State Executive Council]] (EXCO) is appointed from members of the State Assembly. Led by the [[List of Menteris Besar of Johor|Menteri Besar]], it exercises executive power on behalf of the Sultan and is responsible to the State Assembly.\n\n==Speakers Roll of Honour==\n{{empty section|date=November 2018}}\n== Election pendulum ==\nThe 14th General Election witnessed 36 governmental seats and 20 non-governmental seats filled the [[Johor State Legislative Assembly]]. The government side has 12 safe seats and 7 fairly safe seats, while the non-government side has 4 safe seats and 3 fairly safe seats.{{cot|[[Johor state election, 2018|2018 Johor state election]]}}\n{| class=\"toccolours\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"float:left; margin-right:.5em; margin-top:.4em; font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"  style=\"text-align:center; background:red;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">'''GOVERNMENT SEATS'''</span>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"  style=\"text-align:center; background:red;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">'''Marginal'''</span>\n|-\n| Semerah || Mohd. Khuzzan Abu Bakar || PKR || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 42.84\n|-\n| Pemanis || Chong Fat Full || PKR || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 45.14\n|-\n| Senggarang || Khairuddin A. Rahim || AMANAH || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 45.90\n|-\n| Mahkota || Muhamad Said Jonit || AMANAH || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 48.24\n|-\n| Bukit Naning || Md. Ysahruddin Kusni || PKR || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 48.38\n|-\n| Bukit Kepong || Sahruddin Jamal || BERSATU || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 48.98\n|-\n| Serom || Faizul Amri Adnan || AMANAH || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 49.20\n|-\n| Pulai Sebatang || Muhammad Taqiuddin Che'man || AMANAH || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 50.73\n|-\n| Tenang || Mohd. Solihan Badri || BERSATU || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 50.92\n|-\n| Paloh || Sheikh Umar Bagharib Ali || DAP || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 52.10\n|-\n| Tiram || Gopalakrishnan Subramaniam || PKR || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 52.71\n|-\n| Bukit Permai || Tosrin Jarvanthi || BERSATU || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 52